# Movie Credits Website PRD - Todo.txt

# PHILOSOPHY
# - Create a lightning-fast, text-only, ad-free movie credits resource.
# - Replicate the classic end-credits experience (white on black, scrolling).
# - Prioritize searchability and completeness of data.
# - Build a community-driven platform for data acquisition.
# - Monetize ethically through affiliate links, without compromising user experience.

# MVP - CORE FUNCTIONALITY
# ========================

# Backend & Database Setup
- (B) Choose and set up a primary database (e.g., PostgreSQL, MongoDB).
- (B) Design database schema for movies (title, year, etc.).
- (B) Design database schema for credits (department, role, name).
- (B) Create initial API endpoints for movie search (e.g., GET /api/movies/search).
- (B) Create API endpoint to retrieve full credits for a specific movie (e.g., GET /api/movies/:id/credits).
- (B) Set up basic server environment (e.g., Node.js/Express, Python/FastAPI).
- (B) Implement basic logging for API requests and errors.

# Frontend Development
- (F) Initialize a lightweight frontend framework (e.g., Svelte, Vue.js, or even vanilla JS).
- (F) Create the main search page with a single, prominent search bar.
- (F) Develop the search results display logic.
- (F) Create the movie credits page view.
- (F) Style the credits page with a black background and white text.
- (F) Implement the "scrolling credits" mode with a toggle switch (JS animation).
- (F) Ensure the scrolling speed is adjustable by the user.
- (F) Design the site to be fully responsive and accessible.
- (F) Ensure no images or ad-serving scripts are included in the MVP.

# Deployment & Initial Launch
- (D) Choose a hosting provider for the backend (e.g., Vercel, Heroku, DigitalOcean).
- (D) Choose a hosting provider for the frontend (e.g., Vercel, Netlify).
- (D) Set up a domain and configure DNS.
- (D) Create a simple deployment pipeline for continuous integration/delivery.
- (D) Manually enter 5-10 classic movies and their full credits to seed the database.
- (D) Conduct internal testing of search and credits display.
- (D) Launch the MVP to the public.

